2
00:00:00.610 --> 00:00:03.610
Hashiridase hashiridase

3
00:00:00.710 --> 00:00:03.370
Get moving right now, get moving right now

4
00:00:03.590 --> 00:00:06.460
Hoisting our flag high, we'll make it somehow

5
00:00:03.610 --> 00:00:06.610
Sora takaku hata kazashi

6
00:00:12.700 --> 00:00:15.950
Hatenai kono umi wo koete

7
00:00:12.770 --> 00:00:15.500
Setting out all on our own to cross the endless sea,

8
00:00:15.500 --> 00:00:18.060
you know what we're searching for

9
00:00:15.950 --> 00:00:18.210
Sagashi ni yukou yo

10
00:00:18.790 --> 00:00:22.000
Dare mo ima da mitsukerarenai

11
00:00:18.860 --> 00:00:21.810
The worldwide enigma, treasures undiscovered

12
00:00:21.900 --> 00:00:23.940
Picking's ripe, so let's go explore

13
00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:24.000
Sekai no kiseki wo

14
00:00:24.750 --> 00:00:27.920
Takanaru mune omoi no mama

15
00:00:24.820 --> 00:00:27.960
We're all so excited, our hearts can't keep quiet

16
00:00:27.920 --> 00:00:29.970
Tsuki susumu dake sa

17
00:00:27.960 --> 00:00:29.710
Nothing left to do but press on

18
00:00:29.710 --> 00:00:35.590
Trailing after footprints left by the dreamers before us

19
00:00:29.970 --> 00:00:35.680
Yume oibito ga nokosu ashiato wo

20
00:00:36.390 --> 00:00:39.480
Donna arashi no yoru mo

21
00:00:36.420 --> 00:00:39.390
Stormy nights can try their best to sink us

22
00:00:39.390 --> 00:00:42.390
We'll sail on, if we just stick together

23
00:00:39.480 --> 00:00:42.440
Kokoro hitotsu ni sureba

24
00:00:42.390 --> 00:00:46.540
Try and stop us if you can

25
00:00:42.480 --> 00:00:46.610
Koete yukeru yo

26
00:00:46.610 --> 00:00:48.030
Itsudatte

27
00:00:46.680 --> 00:00:47.860
We always pull through

28
00:00:48.700 --> 00:00:51.570
Hashiridase hashiridase

29
00:00:48.760 --> 00:00:51.590
Get moving right now, get moving right now

30
00:00:51.700 --> 00:00:54.580
Sora takaku hatakazashi

31
00:00:51.720 --> 00:00:54.550
Hoisting our flag high, we'll make it somehow

32
00:00:54.580 --> 00:00:57.120
Dare ni mo misenai

33
00:00:54.600 --> 00:00:57.140
Even if we sometimes shed tears,

34
00:00:57.120 --> 00:01:00.540
Namida mo aru keredo

35
00:00:57.230 --> 00:01:00.580
and want to hide them from prying eyes

36
00:01:00.750 --> 00:01:03.630
Oikakete oikakete

37
00:01:00.770 --> 00:01:03.520
But go and chase it, yeah, go and chase it

38
00:01:03.670 --> 00:01:06.630
Yume wo sasu COMPASS wa

39
00:01:03.690 --> 00:01:06.520
Run the direction the compass points in

40
00:01:06.610 --> 00:01:09.230
All our dreams are straight ahead it says

41
00:01:06.630 --> 00:01:09.170
Massugu na hitomi sa

42
00:01:09.170 --> 00:01:11.510
Tachidomarenai

43
00:01:09.230 --> 00:01:11.400
So don't sit back, let's chase it

44
00:01:11.510 --> 00:01:14.470
AROUND THE WORLD

45
00:01:14.510 --> 00:01:16.010
START ME UP!

46
00:01:18.770 --> 00:01:21.600
Hashiridase hashiridase

47
00:01:18.830 --> 00:01:21.490
Get moving right now, get moving right now

48
00:01:21.730 --> 00:01:24.610
Dare yori mo sono saki he

49
00:01:21.800 --> 00:01:24.540
We have to pull through ahead of them all

50
00:01:24.610 --> 00:01:27.150
Nigedasanakereba

51
00:01:24.630 --> 00:01:27.120
If we hold firm and stand our ground,

52
00:01:27.150 --> 00:01:30.490
Ashita wo tsukamerunda

53
00:01:27.220 --> 00:01:30.540
I know the future's within our grasp

54
00:01:30.530 --> 00:01:33.620
Oikakete oikakete

55
00:01:30.600 --> 00:01:33.630
So go and chase it, yeah, go and chase it

56
00:01:33.660 --> 00:01:36.620
Me ni utsuru subete ima

57
00:01:33.680 --> 00:01:36.510
The world's our oyster, it's waiting for us

58
00:01:36.560 --> 00:01:38.930
All the sadness and the joy we see,

59
00:01:36.620 --> 00:01:39.120
Masshiro na kokoro ni

60
00:01:39.120 --> 00:01:41.500
Shirushite yukou

61
00:01:39.150 --> 00:01:41.430
let's etch it in our hearts

62
00:01:41.580 --> 00:01:44.460
BRAND NEW WORLD

63
00:01:44.500 --> 00:01:46.040
START ME UP!

64
00:01:50.050 --> 00:01:55.220
You're Fired

65
00:01:55.220 --> 00:01:58.680
H-Hey! I know that swordsman!

66
00:01:58.680 --> 00:02:02.140
Yeah, he's one of Straw Hat's underlings,
Pirate Hunter Zoro!

67
00:02:03.390 --> 00:02:04.690
Hey, you're an underling.

68
00:02:04.690 --> 00:02:07.190
Which puts you even lower in the ranking...

69
00:02:07.190 --> 00:02:08.520
right, Pirate A?

70
00:02:09.030 --> 00:02:10.070
Huh?!

71
00:02:10.070 --> 00:02:11.360
How about B?

72
00:02:11.360 --> 00:02:12.490
Huh?!

73
00:02:12.490 --> 00:02:15.870
Dammit! When I get a bounty,
it'll be twice as big as yours!

74
00:02:15.870 --> 00:02:16.950
Sure, C.

75
00:02:16.950 --> 00:02:18.910
Don't just ignore me!

76
00:02:18.910 --> 00:02:20.750
Hey, stop it, you two...

77
00:02:20.750 --> 00:02:22.660
Sogeking, they can't hear you.

78
00:02:22.660 --> 00:02:24.710
All according to plan, Sir Chopper.

79
00:02:24.710 --> 00:02:27.460
Oh, I didn't know that.

80
00:02:27.840 --> 00:02:29.460
More are coming from the train!

81
00:02:29.460 --> 00:02:30.340
– They saw us!
– They saw us!

82
00:02:30.340 --> 00:02:31.380
There must be more!

83
00:02:31.380 --> 00:02:33.010
Blow it up before they get out!

84
00:02:33.010 --> 00:02:33.970
Hey, hold it!

85
00:02:33.970 --> 00:02:35.430
Nami is still inside!

86
00:02:35.430 --> 00:02:36.800
Fire!

87
00:02:42.890 --> 00:02:45.400
Man! That was a surpr–

88
00:02:48.150 --> 00:02:49.820
Are you okay, Sogeking?

89
00:02:51.150 --> 00:02:53.440
I-I-I'm okay, Sir Chopper.

90
00:02:53.440 --> 00:02:55.110
Cease fire!

91
00:02:55.700 --> 00:02:56.910
Why's that?

92
00:02:56.910 --> 00:02:57.990
Just look!

93
00:02:57.990 --> 00:02:59.830
– Hello!
– Hello!

94
00:02:59.830 --> 00:03:02.700
Stop it! I'm a senior citizen!

95
00:03:02.700 --> 00:03:06.250
And I'm just a little kid with
a small animal! We're defenseless!

96
00:03:07.790 --> 00:03:13.880
The Straw Hat Pirates threatened me
and made me operate the train!

97
00:03:13.880 --> 00:03:15.510
They did!

98
00:03:21.640 --> 00:03:23.730
Who lets their hostages drink?

99
00:03:23.730 --> 00:03:24.850
That was close!

100
00:03:24.850 --> 00:03:26.850
We could've killed the hostages!

101
00:03:26.850 --> 00:03:32.110
To think those pirates took a senior citizen,
a little kid, and a small animal hostage.

102
00:03:32.110 --> 00:03:32.690
– Huh?
– Huh?

103
00:03:32.690 --> 00:03:34.070
What the...?

104
00:03:34.070 --> 00:03:36.700
That smoke looks like a cloud.

105
00:03:37.070 --> 00:03:40.240
By merging cool balls and heat balls,

106
00:03:40.740 --> 00:03:43.330
the moisture in the air condenses into clouds.

107
00:03:43.330 --> 00:03:45.500
Nami my sweet!

108
00:03:45.500 --> 00:03:47.670
So you escaped the attack!

109
00:03:49.830 --> 00:03:52.550
It is the Perfect Climate Baton, after all.

110
00:03:52.550 --> 00:03:55.550
Its clouds are bigger,
and they develop faster, too.

111
00:03:55.880 --> 00:03:58.510
Now, time to test the new and improved...

112
00:03:58.890 --> 00:04:00.600
thunderbolt!

113
00:04:01.300 --> 00:04:06.060
I don't know what that girl intends to do,
but we need to clear the area!

114
00:04:06.520 --> 00:04:08.980
Here it comes!

115
00:04:09.480 --> 00:04:13.480
Thunderbolt Tempo!

116
00:04:24.200 --> 00:04:30.170
Nooo!

117
00:04:30.710 --> 00:04:32.540
It's gonna kill us too!

118
00:04:32.540 --> 00:04:33.840
Sogeking!

119
00:04:33.840 --> 00:04:35.670
Nami! Why'd you hit Sogeking?!

120
00:04:36.760 --> 00:04:38.880
He knows why.

121
00:04:38.880 --> 00:04:40.590
D-Don't take it out on me.

122
00:04:40.590 --> 00:04:43.260
The problem lies in how you're using it.

123
00:04:43.260 --> 00:04:47.600
Anyway, Sir Usopp said there isn't
a feature for distinguishing foes.

124
00:04:47.600 --> 00:04:48.810
Regardless,

125
00:04:49.810 --> 00:04:51.810
that thing packs a punch!

126
00:04:51.810 --> 00:04:53.060
You took out a bunch.

127
00:04:56.820 --> 00:04:58.190
Screw you, Nami!

128
00:04:58.190 --> 00:04:59.950
What the hell did you do that for?!

129
00:04:59.950 --> 00:05:01.950
Apologize to him, Sogeking!

130
00:05:01.950 --> 00:05:03.700
You apologize, you flake!

131
00:05:03.700 --> 00:05:08.830
Nami! That reminded me of the shock
I felt the first time I met you!

132
00:05:08.830 --> 00:05:11.250
Just who are those guys?

133
00:05:11.250 --> 00:05:15.750
I thought that girl was just their backup,
but she's a force to be reckoned with!

134
00:05:17.710 --> 00:05:21.760
Anyway, where's that idiot
who rushed on ahead of us?

135
00:05:21.760 --> 00:05:22.760
Beats me...

136
00:05:22.760 --> 00:05:26.100
The island isn't that small,
so if we're going to find him...

137
00:05:26.850 --> 00:05:27.520
What?!

138
00:05:29.770 --> 00:05:32.140
– That's definitely him!
– That's definitely him!

139
00:05:33.980 --> 00:05:35.310
Well then...

140
00:05:35.940 --> 00:05:37.360
...shall we go after him?

141
00:05:44.410 --> 00:05:48.370
How dare a few measly pirates cause a ruckus!

142
00:05:48.370 --> 00:05:50.200
It ends here!

143
00:05:51.250 --> 00:05:52.830
Take this!

144
00:05:53.670 --> 00:05:56.540
Main Island, Enies Lobby

145
00:06:06.850 --> 00:06:09.470
Gum-Gum...

146
00:06:09.890 --> 00:06:10.890
Spear!

147
00:06:16.310 --> 00:06:18.020
He jumped onto the tree!

148
00:06:20.230 --> 00:06:24.110
These guys suck! They keep coming!
I can't get through like this!

149
00:06:24.110 --> 00:06:25.950
Hey, this way!

150
00:06:26.820 --> 00:06:28.450
They're running the other way?!

151
00:06:28.450 --> 00:06:31.160
Half of you, go to the island gate!

152
00:06:31.160 --> 00:06:33.960
Invading pirates have broken through!

153
00:06:33.960 --> 00:06:35.630
Stop them at any cost!

154
00:06:35.630 --> 00:06:37.880
They made it! That's great!

155
00:06:37.880 --> 00:06:40.090
This'll be much easier now!

156
00:06:41.170 --> 00:06:42.340
Bull's-eye!

157
00:06:42.340 --> 00:06:43.670
Too bad! You missed!

158
00:06:43.670 --> 00:06:46.180
There he goes! Fire!

159
00:06:45.340 --> 00:06:48.010
Main Island
At the Island Gate

160
00:06:52.430 --> 00:06:54.390
Wh-Why did you stop?

161
00:07:06.450 --> 00:07:09.410
We are the Watchdogs,
keepers of the island gate!

162
00:07:10.700 --> 00:07:14.000
Not a single one of you will cross this line!

163
00:07:14.000 --> 00:07:16.750
Just give up, you damn criminals!

164
00:07:29.050 --> 00:07:31.600
Looks like we're completely surrounded.

165
00:07:31.600 --> 00:07:33.980
– There are just way too many enemies!
– There are just way too many enemies!

166
00:07:34.730 --> 00:07:36.810
And what about it?

167
00:07:37.140 --> 00:07:39.440
You sure talk big for a dead man!

168
00:07:39.440 --> 00:07:40.440
Men, atta–

169
00:07:49.070 --> 00:07:50.490
Grab hold!

170
00:08:08.550 --> 00:08:12.390
Man, you could've let us have a little fun.

171
00:08:11.680 --> 00:08:13.100
You idiot!

172
00:08:13.890 --> 00:08:16.100
Don't forget why you came here.

173
00:08:16.100 --> 00:08:18.560
This is not the time to "have a little fun."

174
00:08:18.940 --> 00:08:23.110
Yeah, it'd probably take the entire day
to fight this many enemies.

175
00:08:26.650 --> 00:08:29.070
They're quite energetic.

176
00:08:29.070 --> 00:08:31.570
Don't die, okay?!

177
00:08:31.570 --> 00:08:33.660
Charge straight ahead!

178
00:08:37.040 --> 00:08:39.120
Guards! Get back!

179
00:08:39.120 --> 00:08:41.130
That's a king bull from Water Seven!

180
00:08:41.130 --> 00:08:43.090
Prepare the cannons immediately!

181
00:08:46.210 --> 00:08:48.220
Dammit!

182
00:08:48.220 --> 00:08:49.680
Take this!

183
00:08:54.100 --> 00:08:56.810
We've got one more!

184
00:08:59.770 --> 00:09:02.310
Watchdogs! Get back in formation!

185
00:09:02.310 --> 00:09:03.690
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

186
00:09:03.690 --> 00:09:05.190
You can't outrun us!

187
00:09:05.190 --> 00:09:08.690
Our dogs are faster than your fish!

188
00:09:09.820 --> 00:09:12.700
This is bad! They're gonna jump up!

189
00:09:12.700 --> 00:09:13.660
How?!

190
00:09:13.660 --> 00:09:15.030
Can't we go faster?!

191
00:09:15.030 --> 00:09:16.790
Hey, cook guy.

192
00:09:16.790 --> 00:09:17.830
Huh?

193
00:09:19.160 --> 00:09:20.160
What's up?

194
00:09:21.170 --> 00:09:22.670
Take the reins.

195
00:09:25.630 --> 00:09:27.210
Hey, what're you...?

196
00:09:38.390 --> 00:09:39.930
When you see those guys...

197
00:09:40.850 --> 00:09:43.440
tell them...

198
00:09:44.480 --> 00:09:46.820
"You're fired."

199
00:09:48.150 --> 00:09:49.820
You got it.

200
00:09:50.150 --> 00:09:51.990
Jump onto it!

201
00:09:52.660 --> 00:09:54.530
Not happening!

202
00:09:54.530 --> 00:09:57.330
We're counting on you, Galley-La!

203
00:09:57.330 --> 00:10:00.040
I'll skewer you!

204
00:10:00.040 --> 00:10:03.000
Half-Knot Air Drive!

205
00:10:11.510 --> 00:10:13.630
Th-They took out some of the Watchdogs!

206
00:10:14.220 --> 00:10:16.300
Those fools let down their guard!

207
00:10:16.300 --> 00:10:20.640
There's no way ordinary people
can match our speed. Go!

208
00:10:20.640 --> 00:10:21.390
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

209
00:10:21.890 --> 00:10:26.110
We'll run you through before you can blink!

210
00:10:32.740 --> 00:10:34.740
They took out even more!

211
00:10:36.410 --> 00:10:38.030
Who are these guys?!

212
00:10:42.000 --> 00:10:44.830
They're so strong!

213
00:10:52.880 --> 00:10:55.220
Leave these guys to us.

214
00:10:55.260 --> 00:10:59.220
Tower of Justice
Enies Lobby

215
00:11:06.600 --> 00:11:11.650
I see that attitude of yours
is the same as ever, Cutty Flam.

216
00:11:11.650 --> 00:11:16.990
If I had realized sooner
that you were alive and had the blueprints,

217
00:11:16.990 --> 00:11:19.620
I could have spared myself a lot of trouble.

218
00:11:19.950 --> 00:11:26.500
All we ever needed to do was
bring you in for your past crimes!

219
00:11:28.250 --> 00:11:33.760
The real hassle was your old buddy Iceburg.

220
00:11:34.220 --> 00:11:35.380
After Tom died,

221
00:11:35.380 --> 00:11:42.010
Iceburg united the shipyards of Water Seven
and organized them all under one company.

222
00:11:42.010 --> 00:11:46.560
And then, when he likely despised
the World Government, he reached out to them.

223
00:11:46.560 --> 00:11:51.610
He shortly thereafter established his company
as one of their ship suppliers.

224
00:11:52.230 --> 00:11:58.450
He's the president of the shipbuilding company Galley-La
and the mayor of the City of Water, Water Seven.

225
00:11:58.990 --> 00:12:04.250
Iceburg became beloved by the people
and proved himself indispensable to the government,

226
00:12:04.250 --> 00:12:08.580
so we needed to take
great care in dealing with him.

227
00:12:09.670 --> 00:12:13.500
I heard your company's been
building ships for the World Government!

228
00:12:13.500 --> 00:12:17.260
Is this some kinda joke?!
Well, I'm not laughing!

229
00:12:18.050 --> 00:12:21.510
So that's why he made a deal
with the government.

230
00:12:21.510 --> 00:12:24.640
He was a surprisingly clever man.

231
00:12:27.270 --> 00:12:30.980
However, the wind began
to blow in my favor.

232
00:12:30.980 --> 00:12:36.150
Just when I had run out of patience
and was about to take drastic measures,

233
00:12:36.150 --> 00:12:39.610
Admiral Aokiji sent me a bit of good news:

234
00:12:40.030 --> 00:12:46.080
Nico Robin was headed
to Water Seven on a pirate ship.

235
00:12:46.500 --> 00:12:50.750
I calmed myself down with a cup of coffee...

236
00:12:51.130 --> 00:12:56.170
and I planned out every single detail,
including the need for being granted a buster call.

237
00:12:56.170 --> 00:13:00.430
Well, there was a slight change in plans...

238
00:13:00.880 --> 00:13:01.970
But look!

239
00:13:01.970 --> 00:13:07.730
Both triggers for the ancient
weapon's revival are here!

240
00:13:10.600 --> 00:13:11.770
Do you get it?

241
00:13:11.770 --> 00:13:15.730
The winds of the entire world
are blowing in my favor!

242
00:13:23.160 --> 00:13:29.540
And now, the power to overthrow
entire nations as I see fit is in my hands!

243
00:13:31.040 --> 00:13:35.500
Why did Aokiji give you the authority
to exercise a buster call?

244
00:13:57.020 --> 00:14:01.860
You're in no position
to ask questions, you bitch!

245
00:14:02.450 --> 00:14:04.410
Your life wouldn't be worth a damn

246
00:14:04.410 --> 00:14:08.370
if I hadn't recognized
the slight amount of value it now has!

247
00:14:10.830 --> 00:14:14.330
So you should be thanking me! Got it?!

248
00:14:16.090 --> 00:14:20.130
You, the repugnant kin of Ohara,
the land of devils...

249
00:14:20.670 --> 00:14:23.430
Now, listen good.

250
00:14:23.430 --> 00:14:30.600
From now on, you will know pain so severe
that you will constantly wish you were already dead,

251
00:14:30.600 --> 00:14:32.850
so prepare yourself.

252
00:14:32.850 --> 00:14:34.440
We'll hurt you,

253
00:14:34.440 --> 00:14:35.690
use you,

254
00:14:35.690 --> 00:14:37.360
and throw you away into the sea.

255
00:14:37.730 --> 00:14:40.980
That's how deeply sinful your existence is!

256
00:14:46.780 --> 00:14:48.450
Oh, that reminds me!

257
00:14:48.450 --> 00:14:50.620
I got a call earlier.

258
00:14:51.620 --> 00:14:58.090
It was a report that some morons have infiltrated our island
just to reclaim the worthless trash that you are.

259
00:14:59.380 --> 00:15:00.590
They didn't...!

260
00:15:00.590 --> 00:15:09.180
Of course, there's no way Straw Hat Luffy
and his crew haven't been captured by now.

261
00:15:11.010 --> 00:15:13.100
Why do those kids...?

262
00:15:15.480 --> 00:15:21.150
They amounted to nothing more than fodder
before the 10,000 Enies Lobby soldiers.

263
00:15:21.150 --> 00:15:27.030
Since our ship is bound for the prison anyway,
I'll add them to the cargo as gifts.

264
00:15:27.030 --> 00:15:32.240
I'll take them to Impel Down
together with Cutty Flam.

265
00:15:37.830 --> 00:15:39.790
Wait! That wasn't our agreement!

266
00:15:40.130 --> 00:15:44.920
In return for my cooperation, you were
supposed to let them get away safely!

267
00:15:47.550 --> 00:15:50.180
What are you flying off the handle for?

268
00:15:50.180 --> 00:15:54.350
Lucci! Please remind us
exactly what that agreement was.

269
00:15:54.350 --> 00:16:01.440
That the six Straw Hat pirates, excluding Nico Robin,
would leave Water Seven safely.

270
00:16:01.440 --> 00:16:03.730
Yeah, that's right.

271
00:16:03.730 --> 00:16:06.110
Precisely as we discussed, right?

272
00:16:13.240 --> 00:16:18.960
They left Water Seven safely,
and now they've come here.

273
00:16:20.420 --> 00:16:22.170
What?!

274
00:16:23.300 --> 00:16:24.380
No...!

275
00:16:24.380 --> 00:16:27.340
You're breaking the deal
using such twisted logic!

276
00:16:28.340 --> 00:16:30.680
They're hopeless scum.

277
00:16:30.680 --> 00:16:33.310
They don't have a shred of morality in them.

278
00:16:33.810 --> 00:16:36.230
Huh? What was that?

279
00:16:37.940 --> 00:16:40.020
Trash shouldn't speak!

280
00:16:40.020 --> 00:16:45.110
To start with, promises made with criminals
don't have to be kept!

281
00:16:45.110 --> 00:16:47.320
Take this! And this, you lowlife!

282
00:16:47.320 --> 00:16:48.740
You too!

283
00:16:50.160 --> 00:16:52.370
Don't get so cocky, you bitch!

284
00:16:52.370 --> 00:16:58.040
The Marines have every right
to use deception in capturing pirates!

285
00:17:06.340 --> 00:17:08.300
You coward...

286
00:17:08.300 --> 00:17:10.630
You're no stranger to betrayal.

287
00:17:10.630 --> 00:17:13.970
Don’t think such a duplicitous bitch
could avoid dying like a dog.

288
00:17:20.980 --> 00:17:25.320
You guys can all die together!

289
00:17:25.320 --> 00:17:29.900
All are helpless
before the immutable power of justice.

290
00:17:37.910 --> 00:17:40.460
Hey, what's that commotion?

291
00:17:47.710 --> 00:17:49.210
Something's coming!

292
00:18:01.770 --> 00:18:03.770
All right, Sodom and Gomorrah!

293
00:18:03.770 --> 00:18:05.900
Keep charging ahead!

294
00:18:08.030 --> 00:18:12.700
Crap! So they're the pirates
who breached the island gate?!

295
00:18:12.700 --> 00:18:15.450
Fire! Keep firing!

296
00:18:16.950 --> 00:18:19.120
Outta the way, or eat dirt!

297
00:18:19.120 --> 00:18:20.660
Take that! And that!

298
00:18:22.790 --> 00:18:25.460
Fall back and reestablish formation!

299
00:18:27.840 --> 00:18:29.250
You're just pirates!

300
00:18:29.250 --> 00:18:31.510
You're not so tough!

301
00:18:37.680 --> 00:18:40.020
Brace yourselves, pirates!

302
00:18:40.020 --> 00:18:42.390
Nooo!

303
00:18:44.810 --> 00:18:46.400
I'm gonna eat you!

304
00:18:46.400 --> 00:18:48.270
Who said you could get on?!

305
00:18:49.520 --> 00:18:50.650
So far so good!

306
00:18:50.650 --> 00:18:52.400
Glad you're on our side!

307
00:18:52.400 --> 00:18:54.950
We need you to take us to Luffy, king bulls!

308
00:18:58.280 --> 00:19:00.450
After him! Don't let him get away!

309
00:19:00.450 --> 00:19:02.660
The enemy is alone! Surround him!

310
00:19:04.410 --> 00:19:05.540
Stop!

311
00:19:05.960 --> 00:19:08.250
Get outta my way!

312
00:19:08.920 --> 00:19:11.210
Don't get in my way!

313
00:19:16.590 --> 00:19:18.550
You bastards!

314
00:19:19.300 --> 00:19:22.640
Commander! He's really scary!

315
00:19:22.640 --> 00:19:25.020
Stand your ground, you maggots!

316
00:19:25.020 --> 00:19:27.350
Go!

317
00:19:28.810 --> 00:19:29.900
Commander!

318
00:19:35.200 --> 00:19:38.030
That... looks like a dead end.

319
00:19:38.490 --> 00:19:40.830
You'd better still be there!

320
00:19:42.450 --> 00:19:45.500
Robin!

321
00:19:47.710 --> 00:19:51.170
Well then, guards, keep these two in chains.

322
00:19:51.170 --> 00:19:51.920
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

323
00:19:52.300 --> 00:19:56.170
Don't ever remove Nico Robin's
seastone handcuffs, understood?

324
00:19:56.170 --> 00:20:00.010
We'll take Cutty Flam to Impel Down
and Nico Robin to Marine Headquarters.

325
00:20:00.010 --> 00:20:04.220
Once the escort ship is ready,
we'll sail through the Gates of Justice.

326
00:20:04.220 --> 00:20:06.180
– Yes, sir! Understood!
– Yes, sir! Understood!

327
00:20:06.180 --> 00:20:07.850
By the way,

328
00:20:08.190 --> 00:20:10.770
there's something you should know.

329
00:20:10.770 --> 00:20:12.270
Cutty Flam is a violen–

330
00:20:14.280 --> 00:20:16.400
So Straw Hat showed up?

331
00:20:15.400 --> 00:20:17.110
He's gnawing on my head! Hey, Kalifa!

332
00:20:17.110 --> 00:20:18.490
That's sexual harassment.

333
00:20:18.490 --> 00:20:19.740
What?!
Yeah...

334
00:20:20.070 --> 00:20:23.330
A call came in earlier.

335
00:20:20.490 --> 00:20:23.830
Hey! Hey! Someone! Someone help! Hey!

336
00:20:23.330 --> 00:20:26.580
The chief was so upset,
it was almost embarrassing.

337
00:20:23.830 --> 00:20:26.580
What're you doing?! Hey!

338
00:20:26.960 --> 00:20:28.460
Let the chief go!

339
00:20:26.960 --> 00:20:30.210
But the report said
that there were only five casualties.

340
00:20:28.460 --> 00:20:30.210
Give up already, you lowlife!

341
00:20:30.210 --> 00:20:31.250
Huh?

342
00:20:34.130 --> 00:20:36.630
The receiver is off the hook.

343
00:20:37.590 --> 00:20:39.380
Don't give us trouble!

344
00:20:39.380 --> 00:20:40.760
Get walking!

345
00:20:52.150 --> 00:20:56.740
You guys go back to your rooms
and take it easy for the time being.

346
00:20:56.740 --> 00:21:02.410
Thanks to this latest success,
CP9's status will undoubtedly skyrocket.

347
00:21:02.410 --> 00:21:05.990
So, shall we raise our glasses on the ship?

348
00:21:08.660 --> 00:21:11.960
I don't feel like drinking...

349
00:21:12.330 --> 00:21:15.210
since I'm not interested in status or authority.

350
00:21:15.210 --> 00:21:16.340
What?

351
00:21:17.300 --> 00:21:21.300
Our justice is whatever
the World Government says it is.

352
00:21:21.300 --> 00:21:25.060
So long as the government
recognizes you as CP9's chief,

353
00:21:25.060 --> 00:21:27.270
we will perfectly carry out our orders.

354
00:21:29.770 --> 00:21:33.730
We don't have to support your ideology.

355
00:21:35.190 --> 00:21:37.320
Th-That's a sound argument.

356
00:21:37.320 --> 00:21:40.360
Then what's in it for you?

357
00:21:44.570 --> 00:21:47.290
Blood, I'd say.

358
00:21:56.840 --> 00:22:00.420
As long as we belong to CP9,
even killing can be justified.

359
00:22:03.090 --> 00:22:05.760
They give me the creeps.

360
00:22:06.180 --> 00:22:10.480
Indeed, they are the government's
principal group of assassins.

361
00:22:10.480 --> 00:22:15.150
My subordinates truly make a dependable unit.

362
00:22:15.150 --> 00:22:20.030
With them at my beck and call,
nothing can stand in my way!

