00:22:32.080 --> 00:22:34.460
Straw Hat Luffy...!

434
00:22:36.420 --> 00:22:39.880
We lost Straw Hat Luffy!

435
00:22:39.880 --> 00:22:43.430
That's just not possible! How many
guards do you think there are?!

436
00:22:43.430 --> 00:22:45.090
But we can't find him anywhere!

437
00:22:45.680 --> 00:22:49.140
Does that mean... he's already
inside the courthouse?!

438
00:22:49.140 --> 00:22:52.640
No, sir! We haven't let even
a single bug through here!

439
00:22:53.890 --> 00:22:55.270
Find him!

440
00:22:55.270 --> 00:22:58.480
Find Straw Hat at any cost!

441
00:23:05.700 --> 00:23:08.490
That must be the last building.

442
00:23:08.490 --> 00:23:10.990
But there's no path to it.

443
00:23:10.990 --> 00:23:13.870
It's a bit far, but I'll try jumping.

444
00:23:18.840 --> 00:23:20.250
What the heck?

445
00:23:20.250 --> 00:23:21.630
Air Door.

446
00:23:32.350 --> 00:23:34.730
You're that bull who was
with the damn pigeon!

447
00:23:34.730 --> 00:23:39.110
The actual situation seems
quite different from the report.

448
00:23:39.110 --> 00:23:41.570
Hey! How'd you do that?!

449
00:23:41.570 --> 00:23:43.570
So cool! Was it a magic trick?

450
00:23:43.570 --> 00:23:48.410
Five casualties certainly seemed
too low a number to be accurate.

451
00:23:48.410 --> 00:23:50.660
Boy, that was a big surprise!

452
00:23:50.660 --> 00:23:53.240
Since the World Government was conceived,

453
00:23:53.240 --> 00:24:00.380
no man has so boldly stepped foot
this far into the government's entrance.

454
00:24:00.380 --> 00:24:04.170
How long do you plan to keep fighting?

455
00:24:17.940 --> 00:24:19.350
Until I die.

456
00:24:26.120 --> 00:24:32.660
I know there’s something that I need to say,

457
00:24:33.040 --> 00:24:36.630
but I can’t seem to find the words

458
00:24:36.880 --> 00:24:44.510
Wandering aimlessly, forever on the hunt, that’s how I’ve lived

459
00:24:44.510 --> 00:24:50.270
And now there’s something right in front of me,

460
00:24:51.470 --> 00:24:54.980
a light that shines brighter than gold

461
00:24:55.350 --> 00:25:00.360
But as I trail behind, it speeds out of sight.

462
00:25:00.360 --> 00:25:06.950
What’s going on? Scared of what’s yet to come

463
00:25:07.280 --> 00:25:13.200
So many times, so many times as we both stumbled on the way

464
00:25:13.410 --> 00:25:16.210
We’ve had our highs, we’ve had our lows;

465
00:25:16.500 --> 00:25:19.290
Yeah, we just take it day by day

466
00:25:19.590 --> 00:25:25.840
Never forget that even when the night snuffs out the light

467
00:25:26.130 --> 00:25:32.470
When the dark has passed the sun will rise again
